hey! popsugar fitness.i have been watching and doing some of your cardio workouts for some time now.But after the workout I feel very Nauseated and uncomfortable. Am i doing something wrong with the work out?

I'm not an expert, but this has happened to me in the past. You usually feel nauseous if you eat or drink too close before a work out or if the intensity of the work out was too high at the time. I say at the time because it varies, you can do the same work out 5 times and have the intensity be too high for 1 or 2 of them, based on whether you've fasted, how much sleep etc.
If you feel nauseous, slow it down and pace around slowly. I find stopping exercise completely can make the nausea worse. I hope that helps :)
